&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s the role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work with our customers (employers and resellers) to deliver a customized version of ALEX that will delight and truly help employees make smart benefits decisions. You will become an expert in employee benefit plans so that you can work closely with our customers to understand benefit offerings, enter those offerings into our system, launch the product, and provide ongoing product support. You will also support renewal pitches, ensure customer information fits within our product, deliver information to customers, manage timelines, handle custom requests, and cultivate positive and personable relationships with customers and coworkers alike. Associate Implementation Managers work closely with Jellyvision’s internal teams to ensure products are delivered in a way that meets customer needs. When not focused on customer work, you’ll support a variety of internal projects, from process documentation to cross-team collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do to be successful&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1) Implement and deliver ALEX to customers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze customer benefit packages and customer-specific software builds to determine fit with Jellyvision’s proprietary software. Don’t worry if you don’t have benefits experience! It’s definitely a nice-to-have, but we can also help you learn along the way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document and communicate any customer-product fit issues you identify both internally and externally and propose ways to resolve them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the team to execute individual “releases” of ALEX for customers to review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep each customer release on track, even when you are feeling the pressure from our seasonal business. We try to mitigate it, but we need to be honest: we are really, really busy from mid-August through mid-November.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We’ll measure success by the timeliness and accuracy of product and feature delivery.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2) Troubleshoot customer issues and resolve them delightfully&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build excellent rapport with customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate project schedules and progress to customers so that they always know where we are in completing each release.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using your product expertise, suggest options for custom-built content to address customers’ unique needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document customer-specific issues and custom work for use in future years.&amp

